    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="1125"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1125">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ecuadorian Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Córdova</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-13">
                        <hi rend="italic">January 13, 1915</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="flushleft">No. 16]</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 25th ultimo, in further relation to the representations that
                    have been made by France and Great Britain to Ecuador in regard to the alleged
                    violation of neutrality by Ecuador in permitting German men-of-war to use the
                    Galápagos Islands as a base of supplies and observation.</p>
                <pb facs="1024" n="710" xml:id="pg_710"/>
                <p>In reply I have the honor to inform you that the Department has communicated to
                    the French and British Embassies the substance of your note, and the substance
                    of that part of your note of December 3, 1914,<note n="1" xml:id="d1125fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_694">p. 694</ref>.</note>
                    which treats of the violation of Ecuadorian neutrality in the Galápagos
                    Islands.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
